"cei":{"d":"‘that will from now on be called ...’ (main verb follows)","n":"When the construct 'the main verb of a clause + {cei} + {broda} series' is used the following usage of {broda} references the whole clause.","e":"i mi ba klama cei broda le zarci i au do broda — I will go to the store. I'd like you go there too.%i le'e verba mlatu cei broda zo'u mi nelci le'e broda poi blabi gi'e ku'i na nelci le'e broda poi xekri — As for kittens I like white ones but don't like black ones."},
"cenba":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ varies in ‘x2(amount of x1, property of x1)’ in amount $x_3 (entity)$ ...","n":"{binxo} describes that entity turns into another entity, {galfi} is ‘to turn one entity into another one’. {cenba} describes how entity changes its state while remaining the same entity, {stika} is ‘to make entity change its state’.","k":"{cenba}, {galfi}, {stika}, {stodi}, {zasni}, {binxo}","e":"i do cenba le ka ma kau se cpedu vau le barda — Your demands vary to much degree.%i ro linji ka'e cenba le ka clani ma kau vau ro da — Any line segment can be changed in its length to any degree.","r":["cenba","cenby"]},
