"ga":{"d":"‘and/or’","n":"used to connect nouns, adverbs, verbs, clauses. Shows that at least one of the constructs inside {ga} ... {gi} is true.","e":"i ga mi citka gi mi kelci — I either eat or play, or do both."},
"ga'a":{"d":"‘to observer ...’, ‘observed by ...’, adverb: ‘being observed’","n":"not limited to vision. When used as a preposition (with a noun after it) the clause itself describes what is being observed. When used after {ne} the clause itself describes sense via one observes.","e":"i ga'a mi ca cerni — To me it's morning now."},
