"galfi":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ transforms, modifies, changes $x_2 (entity)$ into $x_3 (entity)$ ","n":"{binxo} describes that entity turns into another entity, {galfi} is ‘to turn one entity into another one’. {cenba} describes how entity changes its state while remaining the same entity, {stika} is ‘to make entity change its state’.","k":"{stika}, {binxo}, {cenba}, {zasni}","e":"i le mi'u mamta pu galfi le mi'u rectu jo'u le mi'u nanba le pluka snuji — Mother turned the meat and the bread into lovely sandwiches.%i ju'o le mi'u ninmu ba galfi la kevin le speni be vo'a — I'm sure she will make Kevin her spouse.%i le lenku brife pu galfi le mi'u pezli le bunre — The cold wind turned the leaves brown.","r":["galfi","galfy"]},
"galtu":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ is high when viewed from $x_2 (entity)$ and compared to ''x3; x1 is an upper part of x2","k":"{gapru}, {dizlo}, {cnita}, {drudi}, {farna}","e":"i le cipni poi ca'o vofli cu galtu mi lei cmana — To me the flying bird is high above the mountains.","r":["galtu","galty"]},
