"ka":{"d":"turn clause into infinitive","n":"x1 (property) is the property of the clause that follows. Has at least one {ce'u} inside being applied to a noun of the outer clause. {ka} without a {ce'u} inside is the same as {ka ce'u}. Used to express infinitives.","e":"i mi djica le ka sipna — I want to sleep.%i ta'i ku do ba cirko le ka sinma ce'u — This way you will lose respect.%i le ka pendo ku po'o cu tadji le ka se pendo — The only way to have a friend is to be a friend."},
