"megdo":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ is a million of ‘x2(same type as x1)’ in ‘x3(property of x1)’ ","n":"by default, x3 specifies the number of units.","k":"{centi}","e":"i mi ponse le megdo be le rupnu be li ci — I own three million dollars.%i e'o do cuxna fi le pixra poi klani le megdo be li su'e pa bei le ka se bitni li bi — Please choose an image that does not exceed 1 Megabyte.","r":["megdo","megdy"]},
"mei":{"d":"turn number into verb denoting quantity","n":"x1(entity) are (n) in number and are among x2(entity). The number (n) is put in front of {mei}.","k":"{cmima}, {gunma}, {moi}","e":"i mi'o re mei — You and I are two.%i pa mei le nabmi — It is one of the problems.%i le mi'u vo mei pu klama le mi'u kumfa — The four entered the room."},
"mekso":{"d":"$x_1 (text)$ is a mathematical expression under rules $x_2 (proposition)$ ","k":"{cmaci}, {dilcu}, {fancu}, {frinu}, {jalge}, {namcu}, {parbi}, {pilji}","e":"i lu li vo du li re su'i re li'u mekso la lojban — {li vo du li resu'i re} is a mathematical expression in Lojban.%i zoi cy.(x+15&~15).cy. mekso le bangu poi du la c — &quot;(x+15&~15)&quot; is a mathematical expression in C language.","r":["mekso","meksy"]},
"melbi":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ is beautiful to observer $x_2 (entity)$ in aspect ‘x3(property of x1)’ ...","k":"{pluka}, {xamgu}","e":"i le mi'u ninmu cu melbi mi le ka se catlu — For me the woman is beautiful to look at.","r":["melbi","melby"]},
"menli":{"d":"$x_1 (clause)$ is a mind of body $x_2 (entity)$ ","n":"ability of being aware of things and of rational thought.","k":"{intele}, {besna}, {morji}, {mucti}, {pensi}, {sanji}, {xanri}, {sevzi}, {xadni}","e":"i le menli be le smani cu simsa le menli be le remna — The mind of monkeys is similar to the one of humans.","r":["menli","menly"]},
"mensi":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ is a sister of $x_2 (entity)$ by bond ‘x3(property of x1)’ ","k":"{bruna}, {tunba}, {tamne}, {famti}","e":"i do mensi mi le ka se patfu — You are my brother since we are born from the same father.","r":["mensi","mensy"]},
"mentu":{"d":"$x_1 (clause)$ is $x_2 (number)$ minutes long ...","n":"if x2 is not used denotes one minute in duration","k":"{junla}, {cacra}, {snidu}, {tcika}","e":"i le mi'u nu penmi cu mentu be li ji'i xa no — The meeting is approximately 60 minutes long.","r":["mentu","menty"]},
"merko":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ is U.S. American in ‘x2(property of x1)’ ","k":"{bemro}, {ketco}, {glico}","e":"i mi'a pu rinsa le mi'u pa merko — We greeted the American.","r":["merko","merky"]},
"merli":{"d":"$x_1 (entity)$ measures $x_2 (entity)$ as $x_3 (number)$ units on scale ‘x4(property of x2 and x3)’ with accuracy $x_5 (number)$","k":"{kancu}, {rupnu}, {fepni}, {dekpu}, {jmagutci}, {minli}, {bunda}, {ckilu}, {gradu}, {satci}, {cimde}, {kramu}, {manri}, {centi}","e":"i mi merli le mi'u jubme li pa le ka mitre vau li pi pa — I measured the length of the table as 1 meter with accuracy 0.1 meters.","r":["merli","merly"]},
"mi":{"d":"‘I’ (the speaker or the speakers)","e":"i mi gleki — I'm happy."},
"mi'a":{"d":"‘we without you’","n":"{mi'ai} is a more vague pronoun.","e":"i mi'a pu casnu do — We were discussing you."},
"mi'ai":{"d":"‘we’ (at least two persons including at least one of the speakers)","n":"English ‘we’. {mi'a}, {mi'o} and {ma'a} are more specific cases of {mi'ai}. Mostly used to more precisely translate texts from other languages..","e":"i mi'ai se rai troci — We try our best.%i mi'ai djuno le krinu — We know the reason.%i da mi'ai nabmi — We have a problem."},
"mi'e":{"d":"‘I am ...’ (self-identification of the speaker), {mi'e} {nai} — ‘I am not’ (denial of the speaker's identity)","e":"i coi mi'e la gleki — Hello, I'm La Gleki.%i lu coi la kevin li'u lu mi'e nai la kevin li'u — &quot;Hello, Kevin!&quot; &quot;I'm not Kevin.&quot;"},
"mi'i":{"d":"‘from center of ... and of distance ... around’","e":"i le za'u xrula cu zvati le cmana mi'i le ki'otre be li ci — The flowers are present on the mountain and three kilometers around of it."},
"mi'o":{"d":"‘you and I’ (the speaker and the listener)","n":"{mi'ai} is a more vague pronoun.","e":"i mi'o ba renvi — You and I will survive."},
