"si":{"d":"erases one last Lojban word. non-Lojban text is treated as one word","e":"i au mi citka le pa kokso si perli — I'd like to eat a coconut, no, pear!%i mi pu cusku zoi gy.hello, friends!.gy. si zoi gy.hello, kids!.gy. — I said &quot;Hello, friends!&quot;, ehm, no, &quot;Hello, kids!&quot;"},
"si'a":{"d":"‘similarly’, {si'a} {nai} — ‘not similarly’","n":"{ji'a} means ‘additionally’, {si'a} means ‘similarly’ implying that there is another salient difference.","k":"{simsa}, {panra}","e":"i mi si'a pu vitke le mi'u tcadu i sa'u go'i ca pa drata nanca — I also visited the city (just in another year).%i mi nelci le finpe si'a nai — But i like fish."},
"si'au":{"d":"‘It seems’","e":"i si'au le mi'u fetsi cu xebni do — It seems, she hates you.%i si'au le mi'u ctuca pu na pacna — It seems, the teacher was disappointed."},
"si'e":{"d":"turn number into verb denoting portion of a mass","n":"x1(entity) is the n-th part of mass x2(entity). The number (n) is put in front of {si'e}, {pi} {mu} here would mean ‘0.5’, i.e. ‘half’.","e":"i le stati cu kakne le ka zukte su'o zabna i ku'i le go'i cu mo'a si'e lei se gugde — Smart people can do nice things. But they represent a too small fraction of citizens.%i le stati prenu cu kakne le ka zukte le zabna i ku'i le stati cu mo'a si'e lei se gugde prenu — Smart people can do nice things. But they represent a too small fraction of citizens."},
"si'o":{"d":"turn clause into verb","n":"x1 (clause) is a concept described in the clause that follows.","e":"i mi nelci le si'o xunre — I like the color red."},
"si'u":{"d":"‘with the help of ...’","n":"in the clause where {si'u} is used x1 is the one being helped, the help itself is described by the clause.","e":"i le mi'u verba ca kakne le ka cadzu vau si'u le rirni — The child is able to walk now with the help of parents."},
